description:
The Blue Fox is the deadliest mercenary the world has ever known. She is both master thief and relentless assassin. Her victims don't see her coming and her marks never even know she was there. She is a masterless warrior whose services are for sale to the highest bidder. She's also the only one who knows the whereabouts of Mr. Gold.

Will Captain Canuck meet her price or meet her blade?

Also available with a photo cover with Paul Amos as Mr. Gold.

description: Carver's brutal past fianlly catches up to him in Paris, when the reunion with his old flame is cut short in a hail of gunfire. He and Catherine will have to work together to escape their jam, but ultimately Carver will have to unleash his savage nature if they are to survive!

Comic Shop News is comics' weekly newsletter. Each issue is full-color, 8-12 pages in length, and features CSNsider, news, and interviews. CSN has a complete monthly checklist (complete with PREVIEWS item codes), plus exclusive CSN Hot Picks, "Fab Firsts," and a monthly checklist of all the first issues for the month!

Getting to the airport is always a hassle. Getting a Russian mobster to the airport for trial relocation while avoiding The Punisher and mob associates can be deadly! Daredevil has trained Blindspot well, but nothing can prepare him for what will happen next!
name: Chapter Four

description: Find out what happened to Aquawoman during the Battle of Britain, as she is stripped of her powers and captured by Nereus as a prisoner of war.
name: Love Stories Part 1 of 3

description:
Ordo is accursed... Born on the sixth day of the sixth moon, he is the sixth child of a family aligned with the Order of Retaliation. On his sixth birthday, his father abandons him to the instructors of the Black Lodge, a secret branch of the Order which trains assassins destined to eliminate all those who are opposed to the Order's plans.

Thirty years later, Ordo has become a Master of the Shadows, the worst of the Order's assassins, dreaded by all.
name: Ordo of Retaliation

description: When you're a Dreadnaught, a member of an elite team of monsters sent on a suicide mission to stop Hitler from raising an undead army, it becomes difficult to use certain figures of speech: In regular civilian life, if one works with the same co-workers long enough, one will "know where the bodies are buried," or if one wanted to be honest with a co-worker one might "pull some skeletons out of the closet." When your coworkers are immortal Frankenstein Monsters it becomes almost impossible to express hyperbole, skeletons and bodies are everywhere. Join us for a literally monstrous good time in ExMortis #5.

The Fourth Planet is the brand new series from Chapterhouse Comics that The Examiner called "evocative and truly cosmic." The quarterly, written by Fred Kennedy and brilliantly illustrated by Miko Maciaszek, sets the stage where a stolen warship loaded with runaway human slaves crashes onto a planet with three warring races, the most advanced of which has only just begun using gunpowder weaponry. Vastly outnumbered, will the humans become the very thing they were running away from? The warship Lightstorm has crashed on an alien planet. Even though its occupants seek only survival, they become unwillingly entangled within the constant warring of the planet's native species.

Britanny's family vacation to Hawaii is cut short when sixty square miles of Pacific Ocean vanishes, replaced by a dome of sprawling desert and ruins of an otherworldly civilization! Outraged that yet another family getaway is ruined, Brit' drags in Gina to fix the ocean "she broke", despite Gina insisting it isn't her fault this time!

King makes a total ass of himself at an important dinner. Check. Dan's political correctness makes him look like a total ass in front of 4Leaf's newest hire, Brett Ross. Check. And Kade, somehow, isn't even a partial ass as he waxes romantic during magick training. So the Clover boys are one for three. Good for them! Plus, "Ladies' Night" continues at Owls, a "gentleman's" club.

Lisa buys a vintage fedora online and everyone admires how cool it makes her look. But when a series of unfortunate events happen to her, she thinks the hat is cursed. Zack thinks it's silly so he takes it from her and his date stands him up. Convinced that it really is bad luck, he gives it to Slater, who loses a big wrestling match. Kelly thinks it's a coincidence and borrows it, resulting in more bad luck. The foul fedora must be destroyed, before its mayhem spreads!

The epic saga of the Shikari Force: Hunters continues as the group journeys into the sewers under Varanasi to fight a nest of an evil serpent race called the Nagas. They also learn the secret of the mysterious Dakini and discover her role in the coming war between Humans and Nagas, a war it is up to the Shikari Force to stop!

Zen pays Leeta more than her fair share for her help in bagging Palomar, who attempts to bribe Tinhead into helping him escape. Master Satva provides Zen with some important insights into his origin. Teela Morava reveals the grisly fate she has planned for Palomar in the stunning conclusion to the Hard Bounty saga!
